person_analysis.overview: Ethan Qiu is a Computer Science student at the University of Toronto focused on applied machine learning, computer vision, and full-stack development. He serves as UTMIST’s Engineering Director for Industry Collaborations and contributes as an ML developer and infrastructure engineer. He previously completed a SWE co-op at General Dynamics Mission Systems–Canada and has built award-winning, demo-ready projects such as ‘Polaris,’ an ML-powered fitness game.
person_analysis.executive_summary: Ethan blends ML and product engineering to ship interactive, real-time systems. With leadership at UTMIST, a GDMS-Canada co-op, and hackathon-proven CV work, he demonstrates strong end-to-end skills—from model-driven pipelines to performant web experiences—grounded in collaborative, community-oriented initiatives.
key_insights: Strong intersection of ML (pose/gesture) with performant web graphics and real-time UX.
Leadership and cross-team coordination via UTMIST Industry Collaborations.
